To get started with this blank [[TiddlyWiki]], you'll need to modify the following tiddlers:
* [[SiteTitle]] & [[SiteSubtitle]]: The title and subtitle of the site, as shown above (after saving, they will also appear in the browser title bar)
* [[MainMenu]]: The menu (usually on the left)
* [[DefaultTiddlers]]: Contains the names of the tiddlers that you want to appear when the TiddlyWiki is opened
You'll also need to enter your username for signing your edits: <<option txtUserName>>

<<importTiddlers>>

<!--{{{-->
<link rel='alternate' type='application/rss+xml' title='RSS' href='index.xml' />
<!--}}}-->

These [[InterfaceOptions]] for customising [[TiddlyWiki]] are saved in your browser

Your username for signing your edits. Write it as a [[WikiWord]] (eg [[JoeBloggs]])

<<option txtUserName>>
<<option chkSaveBackups>> [[SaveBackups]]
<<option chkAutoSave>> [[AutoSave]]
<<option chkRegExpSearch>> [[RegExpSearch]]
<<option chkCaseSensitiveSearch>> [[CaseSensitiveSearch]]
<<option chkAnimate>> [[EnableAnimations]]

----
Also see [[AdvancedOptions]]

/***
|Description	|introduces the {{{graph}}} macro to create and edit graphs in ~WYSIWYGish manner|
|Version		|0.6.5|
|Author		|Yakov Litvin|
|License		|MIT|
|Source		|https://yakovl.github.io/TiddlyWiki_GraphTools/#VisGraphPlugin|
|Credits		|to authors/contributors of vis.js|
(vis.js 4.18.1 inside: both JS and CSS)
!!!Demo
<<graph [[##somewhere]]
  nodes:'[
    {"id": 1, "label": "Node 1"},
    {"id": 2, "label": "Node 2"},
    {"id": 3, "label": "Node 3"},
    {"id": 4, "label": "Node 4"},
    {"id": 5, "label": "Node 5"},
    {"id": 6, "label": "Node 6"},
    {"id": "a", "label": "Node A"},
    {"id": "b", "label": "Node B"}
  ]'
  edges:'[
    {"from": 1, "to": 3},
    {"from": 1, "to": 2},
    {"from": 2, "to": 4},
    {"from": 2, "to": 5},
    {"from": 3, "to": 3},
    {"from": "a", "to": "b"},
    {"from": "b", "to": "a"},
    {"from": 3, "to": "a"}
  ]'
  id:"demoGraph" height: 300px
  manualRearrange
>>Now here's the same graph but editable, give it a try:<<graph [[##somewhere]]
  id:"demoGraphEditable" height: 300px manipulation:true
>>/%
!somewhere
{
	"data": {
		"nodes": [
			{
				"id": 1,
				"label": "Node 1",
				"x": -94,
				"y": 39
			},{
				"id": 2,
				"label": "Node 2",
				"x": -251,
				"y": 41
			},{
				"id": 3,
				"label": "Node 3",
				"x": 67,
				"y": 63
			},{
				"id": 4,
				"label": "Node 4",
				"x": -167,
				"y": -51
			},{
				"id": 5,
				"label": "Node 5",
				"x": -167,
				"y": 108
			},{
				"label": "Node 6",
				"x": 6,
				"y": -48
			},{
				"id": "a",
				"label": "Node A",
				"x": 174,
				"y": -21
			},{
				"id": "b",
				"label": "Node B\nmultiline",
				"x": 167,
				"y": -90
			}
		],
		"edges": [
			{
				"from": 1,
				"to": 3
			},{
				"from": 1,
				"to": 2
			},{
				"from": 2,
				"to": 4
			},{
				"from": 2,

			},{
				"from": 3,

			},{

				"to": "b"
			},{
				"from": "b",
				"to": "a"
			},{
				"from": 3,
				"to": "a"
			}
		]
	},
	"options": {
		"physics": false
	}
}
!%/

!!!Installation
Usual installation (copy-paste/import tiddler, set the {{{systemConfig}}} tag, reload) is enough, but for graph editor to appear correctly, icons should be added. You may install icons in 2 ways:
# download [[icons archive|https://yakovl.github.io/TiddlyWiki_GraphTools/img/vis_network_icons.zip]], unzip, put icons into {{{./img/network/}}} subfolder
** you may use an alternative path instead. To do so, open VisGraphConfig and put it there. For correct interpretation by CSS, the path must be %-encoded ({{{./my%20icons%2C%20sounds/}}} instead of {{{./my icons, sounds/}}}) or just avoid symbols other than latin letters, digits and {{{_}}}
# add the StyleSheetGraphEditorIcons tiddler (containing base64 icons) to your TW (it's simpler to install but adds ~250 KB to your TW size instead of being ~180 KB of icon files loaded on demand)
!!!Usage
{{{
<<graph [[dataAndOptions:]container] [nodes:...] [edges:...] [options:...]
  [width:...] [height:...] [id:...]
  [manipulation[:boolean]] [handlers:handlersJS]>>
}}}
* {{{container}}}  place where to store the data (edges, nodes) and options of the graph: in a separate tiddler ({{{container}}} = {{{[[tiddler name]]}}}), a section inside the same tiddler ({{{container}}} = {{{[[##section]]}}}) or in another one ({{{[[tiddler##section]]}}})
** either the first unnamed param or named {{{dataAndOptions}}}
* {{{nodes}}} and {{{edges}}}  {{{eval}}}ualted expressions describing non-editable nodes and edges {{DDnc{link to a vis.js example showing usage}}}, useful mostly when those should be generated based on some data and for "importing" data that's in JS, not JSON. If {{{container}}} for data is set, are not taken into account
* {{{options}}}  static [[vis.js options|http://visjs.org/docs/network/index.html#options]], like {{{ { nodes: { shape: "box" } } }}} or {{{ { edges: { arrows: { to: { scaleFactor:0.5 } } } } }}} etc. They are merged with options from {{{container}}} with lower priority
* {{{width}}} and {{{height}}}  dimensions of the graph area (any CSS values like %, px, vh etc)
* {{{id}}}  set to the graph container, may be useful for additional styling {{PoGc{add a background-image example (bg-image + bg-size)}}}
* {{{manipulation[:boolean]}}}  enables graph editor. The {{{manipulation}}} syntax enables editor; the extended syntax may be useful with evaluataion of the parameter: {{{manipulation:{{some JavaScript}} }}}
* {{{handlers}}}  additional [[event|http://visjs.org/docs/network/#Events]] [[handlers|http://visjs.org/docs/network/#method_on]] for the network, {{{handlersJS}}} should be in a form like {{jD{
{{{
'{
	click: function(){ alert("ouch!"); },
	doubleClick: function(){ alert("stop it!"); }
}'
}}}
}}}For now, they only have access to what's provided by vis.js which doesn't include {{{network}}} object or all {{{nodes}}} or {{{edges}}}

!!!!Using the editor GUI
The editor supports some hotkeys:
* {{{enter}}} to apply changes, {{{esc}}} to cancel
* {{{shift+enter}}} to insert a linebreak (in a node's label)

!!!!Notes
If {{{container}}} is set to a section which doesn't exist, it is created hidden inside a wiki comment ({{{/% ... %/}}}). In this container data and options are stored as a single JSON object so if you edit it manually, keep that format ({{{ { "name":"value" } }}} is valid JSON while {{{ { name:"value" } }}} is not although this is valid for the {{{eval}}}uated {{{nodes}}}, {{{edges}}} and {{{options}}}).

Although current graph editor doesn't provide access to all the options that vis.js provides, once options of nodes and edges or global options are changed in {{{container}}}, they are preserved after further edits so you can set shapes, colors etc of nodes, labels, arrows etc of edges. For instance, if you find your node in JSON:
{{{
			},{
				"label": "My node",
				"x": -11,
				"y": -131
			},{
}}}
and set
{{{
			},{
				"label": "My node",
				"x": -11,
				"y": -131,
				"shape":"box",
				"color":{ "background":"white", "border":"red"}
			},{
}}}
you'll get a node like this:
<<graph [[##one modified node]] manipulation:true>>/%
!one modified node
{
	"data": {
		"nodes": [
			{
				"x": -237,
				"y": 5,
				"label": "My node",
				"shape":"box",
				"color":{ "background":"white", "border":"red"}
			}
		],
		"edges": []
	},
	"options": {}
}
!%/and go on editing the graph via UI.

The plugin sets some default options to each graph. Currently they are:
| name | value | description |
|{{{interaction}}}|{{{ { multiselect: true } }}}|enables multiselection by ctrl+click|
|{{{nodes}}}	|{{{ { color: { background: "white" } } }}}|makes default nodes' background white|

{{PoGc{add some suggested practices (change all nodes' shapes at once etc}}}
***/

	defaultOptions: {
		interaction: { multiselect: true },
		nodes: { color: { background: "white" } }
	}
};
config.macros.graph.getEvaluated = function(evalExpression) { // a helper
	return eval("(function(){return "+ evalExpression +"})()");
};
config.macros.graph.getStoredDataAndOptions = function(tiddlerTitle,section)
{
	var container = tiddlerTitle + (section ? "##"+section : ""),
	    dataAndOptionsText = store.getTiddlerText(container),
	    dataAndOptions = dataAndOptionsText ? JSON.parse(dataAndOptionsText) : {};
	// storage format can be changed but return value should be
	// { data:{ nodes: [...], edges: [...] }, options: {...} }
	return dataAndOptions;
};
window.advancedMerge = function(reciever, source, preserveExisting)
{
	for(var key in source) {
		if(reciever[key] === undefined)
			reciever[key] = source[key];
		else if(typeof reciever[key] === 'object' && reciever[key] !== null)
			reciever[key] = window.advancedMerge(reciever[key], source[key], preserveExisting);
		else if(!preserveExisting)
			reciever[key] = source[key];
	}
	return reciever;
};
config.macros.graph.handler = function(place,macroName,params,wikifier,paramString,tiddler)
{
	// parse macro params
	var pParams = paramString.parseParams("dataAndOptions",null,true,false, true),
	    storageContainer = getParam(pParams,"dataAndOptions",""),
		tiddlerTitle = tiddler.title, section,
	    userSetId = getParam(pParams,"id",""),
	    width = getParam(pParams,"width",""),
	    height = getParam(pParams,"height",""),
	    nodes = new vis.DataSet(this.getEvaluated(getParam(pParams,"nodes","[]"))),
	    edges = new vis.DataSet(this.getEvaluated(getParam(pParams,"edges","[]"))),
	    defaultManipulation = {
		addNode: function (data, callback) {
			var network = this, container = network.body.container;
			config.macros.graph.createEditPopup(container, "Add Node", data,callback);
		},
		editNode: function (data, callback) {
			var network = this, container = network.body.container;
			config.macros.graph.createEditPopup(container, "Edit Node", data,callback);
		},
		addEdge: function (data, callback) {

			if (data.from == data.to) {
				if (confirm("Do you want to connect the node to itself?"))
					callback(data);
			} else
				callback(data);
		}
	    },
	    useDefaultManipulation = getParam(pParams,"manipulation", paramString.match( /\smanipulation(\s|$)/gm)),
	    macroOptions = this.getEvaluated(getParam(pParams,"options","{}")),
	    handlers = this.getEvaluated(getParam(pParams,"handlers","{}"));
	if(useDefaultManipulation)
		macroOptions.manipulation = defaultManipulation;
	var nonStoredOptions = macroOptions;
	window.advancedMerge(nonStoredOptions, this.defaultOptions, true);
	// defaultOptions has lower priority than macroOptions
	var options = {};

	if(storageContainer) {
		var separator = config.textPrimitives.sectionSeparator,
		    re = new RegExp("^(.*)" + separator + "(.+)$"),
		    match = re.exec(storageContainer);
	    	// storageContainer may be
		tiddlerTitle = (match ? match[1] : // tiddler name##section name
			storageContainer) // tid name
			|| tiddlerTitle; // ##section name
		section = match ? match[2] : "";

		var dataAndOptions = this.getStoredDataAndOptions(tiddlerTitle,section),
		    storedData	   = dataAndOptions.data,
		    storedOptions  = dataAndOptions.options;
		if(storedData) {
			nodes = new vis.DataSet(storedData.nodes);// || nodes;
			edges = new vis.DataSet(storedData.edges);// || edges;
		}
		options = storedOptions || {};
	}
	window.advancedMerge(options,nonStoredOptions,true);

	var data = {
		nodes: nodes,
		edges: edges
	    },
	    stabilizeOnce = getParam(pParams,"stabilizeOnce",
		paramString.match(/\sstabilizeOnce[\s>]/)),
	    manualRearrange = getParam(pParams,"manualRearrange",
		paramString.match(/\smanualRearrange[\s>]/));
	if((manualRearrange !== false) && (manualRearrange != "false") && useDefaultManipulation)
		manualRearrange = true;

	// create a container,
	// show a warning if manipulation was activated but container is not set
	var uniqueId = "visGraph"+Math.floor(Math.random()*1000);
	while(document.getElementById(uniqueId))
		uniqueId += 1;
	var id = userSetId || uniqueId,

	    wrapper = createTiddlyElement(place,"div",null,"visGraphWrapper");
	if(options.manipulation && !storageContainer)
		createTiddlyElement(wrapper,'span',null,'dataLossWarning',
			"Warning: you have enabled manipulation options but haven't set the first unnamed/dataAndOptions parameter so your changes won't be saved anywhere.");
	var container = createTiddlyElement(wrapper,"div",id,"visGraph");

	if(width) container.style.width = width;
	if(height) container.style.height = height;

	// create a network
	var network = new vis.Network(container, data, options);

	// hijack manipulation methods so that their context (this) is network
	var mSettings = options.manipulation;
	if(mSettings) {
		var methods = {addNode:1, addEdge:1, editNode:1, editEdge:1, deleteNode:1, deleteEdge:1};

		for(let methodName in methods) {

			// for edge editing, options have a special case of usage:
			var isEditEdgeAsObject = methodName == 'editEdge' &&
				typeof mSettings.editEdge === 'object';

			if(!(mSettings[methodName] instanceof Function) &&
			   !isEditEdgeAsObject)
				mSettings[methodName] = function (data, callback) {
					callback(data);
				};

			if(isEditEdgeAsObject) {
				if(mSettings.editEdge.editWithoutDrag)
				{
					var editEdge = mSettings.editEdge;
					editEdge.nonSaving_editWithoutDrag =
						editEdge.editWithoutDrag;
					editEdge.editWithoutDrag =
					  function(data,callback) {
						// hijack callback to add saving
						arguments[1] = function() {
							callback.apply(this,arguments);
							config.macros.graph.saveDataAndOptions(network);
						};
						editEdge.nonSaving_editWithoutDrag
							.apply(this,arguments);
					}.bind(network);
				}
			} else {
			  mSettings['nonSaving_'+methodName] = mSettings[methodName];
			  mSettings[methodName] = function(data,callback) {
				// hijack callback to add saving
				arguments[1] = function() {
					callback.apply(this,arguments);
					config.macros.graph.saveDataAndOptions(network);
				};
				mSettings['nonSaving_'+methodName]
					.apply(this,arguments);
			  }.bind(network);
			}
		}
		
		network.setOptions(options);
	}

	// store auxiliary stuff
	network.tw_storageTiddlerTitle = tiddlerTitle;
	network.tw_storageSection = section;
	network.tw_contextTiddlerTitle = tiddler ? tiddler.title : null;
	network.nonStoredOptions = nonStoredOptions;
	// set event handlers
	if(manualRearrange)
		network.on("dragEnd",this.saveToTiddlerAfterDragging);
	for(let type in handlers)
		network.on(type,handlers[type]);

	if(stabilizeOnce)
		network.on("stabilizationIterationsDone", function () {
			network.setOptions( { physics: false } );
		});
};

// helper not to store empty options
var collapsObject = function(obj){
	for(var key in obj) {
		if(typeof obj[key] !== 'object') // typeof null === 'object'
			continue;
		collapsObject(obj[key]);
		//for non-jQuery, see https://stackoverflow.com/a/32108184/3995261
		if(jQuery.isEmptyObject(obj[key])) // returns true for non-objects, at least numbers
			delete obj[key];
	}
};

config.macros.graph.createEditPopup = function(container, operationTitle, data, callback)
{
	var $container = jQuery(container),
	// we attach the popup to the container instead of body, so that it is destroyed when we close the graph
	    $popup = $container.find(".network-popUp"),
	    $title, key, $table, $saveButton, $cancelButton;

	// prepare the popup DOM
	if(!$popup[0])
	{
		$popup = jQuery('<div class="network-popUp"></div>')
				.prependTo($container);
		$title = jQuery('<span class="operation"></span> <br>')
				.appendTo($popup);
		$table = jQuery('<table></table>').appendTo($popup);
		$saveButton = jQuery('<button class="saveButton">save</button>')
				.appendTo($popup);
		$cancelButton = jQuery('<button class="cancelButton">cancel</button>')
				.appendTo($popup);
	} else {
		$title = $popup.find(".operation");
		$table = $popup.find("table");
		$saveButton = $popup.find(".saveButton");
		$cancelButton = $popup.find(".cancelButton");
	}
	$title[0].innerHTML = operationTitle;
	for(key of ['label']) // don't bother user with ids
		$table.append('<tr><td>'+key+'</td><td>'+
		    '<textarea class="dataEditor data-'+key+'">'+data[key]+'</textarea>'+
		'</td></tr>');

	var adjustHeightToContent = function()
	{
		var defaultHeight = 10;
		var maxHeight = 150;
		// take padding into account:
		var computedStyle = window.getComputedStyle(this, null),
		    paddingTop = computedStyle.getPropertyValue('padding-top'),
		    paddingBottom = computedStyle.getPropertyValue('padding-bottom'),
		    padding = parseFloat(paddingTop) + parseFloat(paddingBottom);

		jQuery(this).height(defaultHeight); // needed to descrease the height
		var effectiveHeight = this.scrollHeight - padding;
		jQuery(this).height(Math.min(effectiveHeight, maxHeight));
	};
	jQuery('.dataEditor').on('input',adjustHeightToContent);
	// for textarea to have 1 line height in FF when appropriate,
	// overflow-x: hidden; is used (https://stackoverflow.com/q/7695945/3995261)

	// set handlers to interact with user
	var clearPopUp = function() {
		$saveButton.off();
		$cancelButton.off();
		$popup.off();
		$popup.css({ display: "none" });
		$table.empty();
	};
	var saveData = function() // data,callback  from closure
	{
		$table.find('.dataEditor').each(function(index,inputElement){
			var keyMatch = /\bdata-(\S+)\b/.exec(inputElement.className),
			    key = keyMatch ? keyMatch[1] : null;
			data[key] = inputElement.value;
		});

		// fix applying empty option trees creating undesirable shadows et al.
		collapsObject(data);

		clearPopUp();
		callback(data);
	};
	var cancelEdit = function() // callback  from closure
	{
		clearPopUp();
		callback(null);
	};
	var handleCancel = operationTitle == "Add Node" ? clearPopUp : cancelEdit;

	$saveButton.on('click',saveData);
	$cancelButton.on('click',handleCancel);
	$popup.on('keydown',function(ev){
		if(ev.keyCode == 13 && !ev.shiftKey) { // enter without shift
			saveData();
			ev.cancelBubble = true;
			if(ev.stopPropagation) ev.stopPropagation();
		}
		if(ev.keyCode == 27)
			handleCancel();
	});

	// show the popup and set focus to the first input field
	$popup.css({ display: "block" });
	jQuery('.dataEditor').trigger('input'); // call resizing
	$popup.find(".dataEditor").eq(0).focus().select();
};
// apply the CSS setting the icons, if present
var styleSheetName = "StyleSheetGraphEditorIcons",
    css = store.getTiddlerText(styleSheetName) || "";
config.shadowTiddlers[styleSheetName] = css; //# is shadow even needed here?
store.addNotification(styleSheetName, refreshStyles);

var configName = "VisGraphConfig";
config.shadowTiddlers[configName] = "|iconsPath|./img/network/|";

config.macros.graph.saveDataAndOptions = function(network,newOptions) {

	if(!network) return;
	newOptions = newOptions || {};

	var tiddlerName = network.tw_storageTiddlerTitle;
	var section = network.tw_storageSection;
	if(!tiddlerName) return;

	// get tiddler where to store (fetches if exists and creates otherwise):
	var tiddler = store.createTiddler(tiddlerName);

	// get nodes and edges
	var nodes = network.body.data.nodes._data; // contains id, label, x,y, custom per-node options and doesn't contain options from options.nodes; presumably contains option values set when network was created, not current ones (it is so for x,y)
// network.body.nodes[id].nodeOptions shows options from options.nodes but not custom per-node options (same for edges and network.body.edges[id].edgeOptions)
// network.body.nodes contain much more stuff (x,y, default stuff)
	//# look for a suitable getter
	var edges = network.body.data.edges._data; // map; for edges to/from? certain node use network.getConnectedNodes(id)
	// network.body.data.edges._data is a hash of { id: , from: , to: }

	// get node positions, options
	var positions = network.getPositions(), // map
	    options = config.macros.graph.getStoredDataAndOptions(tiddlerName,section)
		.options,
	    nonStoredOptions = network.nonStoredOptions,
//# get current network options, strip nonStoredOptions from those (implement similarly to advancedMerge), but remember some of them was rewritten by options stored previously
	    storedOptions = options || {};
	window.advancedMerge(storedOptions,newOptions);

	// helper for storing options
	var copyObjectProperties = function(obj) {
		return JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(obj));
	};

	// get JSON with nodes, edges and options for storage
	var storedEdges = [], storedEdge, storedNodes = [], storedNode;
	var indexIds = {}, idIndex = 1, end;

	for(var nodeId in nodes) {
		// nodes[nodeId].x is the initial value, positions[nodeId].x is the current one
		if(positions[nodeId]) { // undefined for hidden
			nodes[nodeId].x = positions[nodeId].x;
			nodes[nodeId].y = positions[nodeId].y;
		}
		storedNode = copyObjectProperties(nodes[nodeId]);

		// don't store id unless that breaks connected edges
		if(!network.getConnectedEdges(nodeId).length)
			storedNode.id = undefined;
		// substitute generated ids with no semantics with simple indices
		if(/\w{8}-\w{4}-\w{4}-\w{4}-\w{12}/.exec(storedNode.id)) {
			while(nodes[idIndex])
				idIndex++;
			indexIds[storedNode.id] = idIndex; // remember the given index
			storedNode.id = idIndex; // substitute with an index
			idIndex++;
		}

		storedNodes.push(storedNode);
	}
	for(var edgeId in edges) {
		storedEdge = copyObjectProperties(edges[edgeId]);
		storedEdge.id = undefined; // then strip id

		// change from/to in accord to the substitution above (for nodes' ids)
		for(end of ["from","to"])
			storedEdge[end] = indexIds[storedEdge[end]] || storedEdge[end];

		storedEdges.push(storedEdge);
	}
	var dataAndOptions = {
		data: {
			nodes: storedNodes,
			edges: storedEdges
		},
		options: storedOptions
	};
	var dataAndOptionsText = JSON.stringify(dataAndOptions,"",4)
		.replace(/ {4}/gm,"\t").replace(/},\n\t\t\t{/gm,"},{");

	// update tiddler text
	if(section)
		tiddler.setHiddenSection(section,dataAndOptionsText);
	else if(tiddler.title != network.tw_contextTiddlerTitle)
		tiddler.text = dataAndOptionsText;
	else
		; //# notify: won't save
	//# notify? refreshing may be good for updating edges' geometry
	store.setDirty(true);
};
config.macros.graph.saveToTiddlerAfterDragging = function(stuff) {

	config.macros.graph.saveDataAndOptions(this,{ physics: false });
};
//}}}
/***
!!! .setHiddenSection helper, copied from HandsontablePlugin
***/
//{{{
// Sets the section value if it is present, appends a hidden one otherwise
// (code adapted from SetManagerPlugin, Tiddler.prototype.setSection)
//
Tiddler.prototype.setHiddenSection = Tiddler.prototype.setHiddenSection || function(sectionName,value)
{
	var beginSectionRegExp = new RegExp("(^!{1,6}[ \t]*" + sectionName.escapeRegExp() + "[ \t]*(\n|$))","mg"),
	    sectionTerminatorRegExp = /^!/mg,
	    match = beginSectionRegExp.exec(this.text);

	if(!match) // no such section, append to the end, but don't break TW tables
	{
		// add empty
		this.text = this.text + (this.text[this.text.length-1] == "|" ? "\n":"") +
			"/%\n!"+sectionName+"\n" + "\n!%/";
		// re-match
		beginSectionRegExp.lastIndex = 0;
		match = beginSectionRegExp.exec(this.text);
	}

	// now change section content (setSection may be used instead)
	var sectionTitle = match[1],
	    emptyAtEnd = match[2] != "\n",
	    beforeSection = this.text.substr(0,match.index),
	    sectionAndAfter = this.text.substr(match.index + match[1].length);

	match = sectionTerminatorRegExp.exec(sectionAndAfter);
	var afterSection = match ? sectionAndAfter.substr(match.index) : "";

	this.text = beforeSection + sectionTitle + (emptyAtEnd ? "\n" : "") +
			value + (afterSection ? ("\n" + afterSection) : "");

	// setting dirty, notifying is not done here
};
//}}}
